<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="360" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,649,856]" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Park" authorityName="Park" authorityYear="2018" box="[275,444,649,675]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Thubdora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[275,385,649,675]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">Thubdora</emphasis>
Park
</taxonomicName>
is one of the largest genera of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gozmany" authorityYear="1978" box="[952,1091,649,675]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Torodorinae">Torodorinae</taxonomicName>
, comprising 39 known species (
<bibRefCitation author="Park, K. - T. &amp; Mey, W. &amp; Koo, J. M. &amp; De Prins, J. &amp; Akite, P. &amp; Cho, S. W." box="[159,357,685,712]" pageId="3" pageNumber="360" pagination="451 - 487" refId="ref10215" refString="Park, K. - T., Mey, W., Koo, J. M., De Prins, J., Akite, P. &amp; Cho, S. W. (2020 a) Fourteen new species of the genus Thubdora Park, 2018 (Lepidoptera: Gelechioidea: Lecithoceridae) from Uganda, with a tentative check list in Afrotropical Region excluding Madagascar. Zootaxa, 4759 (4), 451 - 487. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4759.4.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Park 
<emphasis box="[220,271,685,711]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">et al</emphasis>
. 2020a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Park, K. - T. &amp; Cho, S. W." box="[370,572,685,711]" pageId="3" pageNumber="360" pagination="399 - 409" refId="ref10008" refString="Park, K. - T. &amp; Cho, S. W. (2021) Four new species of Thubdora Park, 2018 and one new species of Torodora Meyrick, 1894 (Lepidoptera, Lecithoceridae, Torodorinae) from Tanzania. Zootaxa, 5068 (3), 399 - 409. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4571.4.1" type="journal article" year="2021">Park &amp; Cho 2021</bibRefCitation>
) in the Afrotropical Region. The genus is superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1891" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Ptilothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1318,1436,685,711]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">Ptilothyris</emphasis>
Walsingham, 1891
</taxonomicName>
, by having a similar venation, but can be distinguished by the antenna not bipectinated, and the forewing not so elongated with more or less rounded apex. The male genitalia are also similar but differentiated from those of the latter by the usually elongated uncus with a truncate or convex caudal margin, or bifurcated apically, whereas it is broadly developed, expanded distally as a fan-shaped plate in 
<emphasis box="[1060,1186,829,855]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1891" box="[1060,1182,829,855]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Ptilothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ptilothyris</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
